genresAdvancedInfo.name: eastern bloc groove
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Eastern bloc groove is a genre of electronic dance music that emerged in the former Eastern Bloc countries of Europe during the 1990s. It is characterized by its use of heavy, driving beats, as well as its incorporation of elements of traditional Eastern European folk music and instrumentation. Eastern bloc groove is often associated with the underground club scenes of cities like Prague, Budapest, and Warsaw, and is known for its dark, atmospheric sound and intense, hypnotic rhythms.
